<item>
            <title>[BEAM-1846] Update os-maven-plugin to 1.5.0.final+ for building shade file on RHEL/CentOS</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-1846</link>
                <project id="12319527" key="BEAM">Beam</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The current os-maven-plugin may export the profile with quote on certain versions of centos/RHEL, and it introduces the error when building shade file. The error message is shown below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
    [ERROR]... Error creating shaded jar: The name &quot;os.detected.release.like.&quot;centos&quot;&quot; is not legal for JDOM/XML elements: XML names cannot contain the character &quot;&quot;&quot;. -&amp;gt; [Help 1]

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The error is caused by the /etc/os-release which contains some quote. The os-maven-plugin 1.4.1.final+ had fixed it. Therefore, we ought to update the os-maven-plugin to latest verison (1.5.0.fianl) for the user who can&#8217;t change the content of the /etc/os-release.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>CentOS</environment>
